			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://melvincarvalho.com/blog/bitcoin-testnet/" title="Permalink to Bitcoin Testnet" rel="bookmark">Bitcoin Testnet</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://melvincarvalho.com/blog/bitcoin-testnet/" title="8:55 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">April 28, 2013</span></a> <span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://melvincarvalho.com/blog/author/admin/" title="View all posts by admin">admin</a></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p>Running the bitcoin testnet is quite easy.  From the command line:</p>
<p>bitcoin-qt -testnet</p>
<p>And allow the client to update</p>
<p>There is also a faucet at: http://testnet.mojocoin.com/</p>
